          <div class="depth-rules-section-label">► THE FORMULA</div>
          <div class="depth-rule-row">
            <span class="depth-rule-key">FORMULA</span>
            <span class="depth-rule-val">SHARK SCORE = SCORE² ÷ TIME (seconds)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="depth-rule-row">
            <span class="depth-rule-key">EXAMPLE</span>
            <span class="depth-rule-val">Score 250 in 90s → 250² ÷ 90 = 694</span>
          </div>
          <div class="depth-rules-section-label" style="margin-top:1.4rem">► DESIGN INTENT</div>
          <div class="depth-rule-row">
            <span class="depth-rule-key">HIGH SCORE</span>
            <span class="depth-rule-val">Matters most — doubling your score quadruples Shark Score.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="depth-rule-row">
            <span class="depth-rule-key">FAST TIME</span>
            <span class="depth-rule-val">Acts as a multiplier — cutting time in half doubles Shark Score.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="depth-rule-row">
            <span class="depth-rule-key">BALANCE</span>
            <span class="depth-rule-val">A high score at average speed still ranks well. Neither extreme dominates.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="depth-rules-section-label" style="margin-top:1.4rem">► ELIGIBILITY</div>
          <div class="depth-rule-row">
            <span class="depth-rule-key">REQUIRED</span>
            <span class="depth-rule-val">You must start the run at Depth 1 — The Shallows. A Shark Score is not generated at all for runs that begin at any other depth.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="depth-rule-row">
            <span class="depth-rule-key">WHY</span>
            <span class="depth-rule-val">The formula measures score versus total time from the very beginning. Starting mid-game would produce an artificially inflated score that can't fairly compare to full runs.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="depth-rules-section-label" style="margin-top:1.4rem">► NOTE</div>
          <div class="depth-rule-row">
            <span class="depth-rule-key">TUNABLE</span>
            <span class="depth-rule-val">The exponent (currently 2) may be adjusted as the game grows to keep the leaderboard meaningful across all score ranges.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
